fields.description:
We do not properly handle certain characters in the URL and produce a link which makes no sense if they are present.  For example, this URL:
{code}
http://172.22.3.56:6060/foo/browse/~tag=bugfix-382-branch-before/sanity1
{code}

the following commit message will add comments and time to the JIRA, but will not create a review.
{code}
CRTES-1 Fix a bug +review CR-TEST
CRTES-1 #time 2h
CRTES-1 #comment Review comments have been incorporated #close
{code}

Hi Mates.

A customer mentioned that this was not working on Fecru 2.8.1 and I was able to reproduce, on Fecru 2.7.X it is working normally:

# Create a new {{Project}}
# Set the group for the {{Allowed Review Participants}} of that Project
# Login with a normal {{User}}
# Create a new {{Review}}
# Edit the {{Details}}
# In the {{Reviewers}} box if you double click on it you will see only the members of the group previous set up in the {{Allowed Review Participants}}, now if you search for the specific username of someone who's not allowed {{Crucible}} his name will be displayed and you can select the user. However after hitting done the permissions are respected and the user is not added to the review.

Thank you in advance.

Cheers,
*Douglas Fabretti*
*Atlassian Support*
